.TH "sclp_sd_sync" 9 "sclp_sd_sync" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sclp_sd_sync \- Perform Store Data request synchronously
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" sclp_sd_sync
.BI "(unsigned long page "  ","
.BI "u8 eq "  ","
.BI "u8 di "  ","
.BI "u64 sat "  ","
.BI "u64 sa "  ","
.BI "u32 *dsize_ptr "  ","
.BI "u32 *esize_ptr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "page" 12
Address of work page - must be below 2GB
.IP "eq" 12
Input EQ value
.IP "di" 12
Input DI value
.IP "sat" 12
Input SAT value
.IP "sa" 12
Input SA value used to specify the address of the target buffer
.IP "dsize_ptr" 12
Optional pointer to input and output DSIZE value
.IP "esize_ptr" 12
Optional pointer to output ESIZE value
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Perform Store Data request with specified parameters and wait for completion.

Return 0 on success and store resulting DSIZE and ESIZE values in
\fIdsize_ptr\fP and \fIesize_ptr\fP (if provided). Return non-zero on error.
